{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641822","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641822"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:32:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:32:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17908"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17908","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17908"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.05,0.1,0.3,0.45]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10622"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78785"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10622","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10622"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17908"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64134"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"11204"},{"type":"tags","id":"11246"},{"type":"tags","id":"11247"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24749"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24751"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78785","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78785"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following proteins is known to mediate leptin resistance in obesity?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["SOCS","G9-alpha-butadine","CTRP4","AMPK","LEPR"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ELeptin is a hormone that assists in the regulation of energy balance through hunger inhibition and is produced by adipose tissue. In obesity, despite high levels of leptin, the body becomes resistant to its effects, a condition known as leptin resistance. This resistance is often mediated by \u003Cstrong\u003ESOCS\u003C/strong\u003E proteins, which interfere with leptin signalling pathways, particularly the JAK-STAT pathway, leading to impaired leptin action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAMPK\u003C/strong\u003E is an enzyme that plays a role in cellular energy homeostasis but is not directly involved in mediating leptin resistance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELEPR\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the leptin receptor, which is involved in leptin signalling but is not a suppressor protein that mediates resistance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECTRP4\u003C/strong\u003E is a member of the C1q/TNF-related protein family and is not directly associated with leptin resistance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EG9-alpha-butadine\u003C/strong\u003E is not a recognised protein involved in leptin signalling or resistance.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Leptin resistance in obesity is mediated by suppressor of cytokine signalling (SOCS) proteins.","SOCS proteins interfere with leptin signalling pathways, contributing to leptin resistance.","Understanding the role of SOCS proteins in leptin resistance can help in developing targeted therapies for obesity."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Judge A, Dodd MS. Metabolism. Essays Biochem. 2020 Oct 8;64(4):607-647. doi: 10.1042/EBC20190041. PMID: 32830223; PMCID: PMC7545035Pathak R, Bridgeman MB. Dipeptidyl Peptidase-4 (DPP-4) Inhibitors In the Management of Diabetes. P T. 2010 Sep;35(9):509-13. PMID: 20975810; PMCID: PMC2957740","Gallwitz B. Clinical Use of DPP-4 Inhibitors. Front Endocrinol (Lausanne). 2019 Jun 19;10:389. doi: 10.3389/fendo.2019.00389. PMID: 31275246; PMCID: PMC6593043","Izquierdo AG, Crujeiras AB, Casanueva FF, Carreira MC. Leptin, Obesity, and Leptin Resistance: Where Are We 25 Years Later? Nutrients. 2019 Nov 8;11(11):2704. doi: 10.3390/nu11112704. PMID: 31717265; PMCID: PMC6893721.","Yeung AY, Tadi P. Physiology, Obesity Neurohormonal Appetite And Satiety Control. 2023 Jan 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32310366"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64134"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17908"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64134","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64134"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-12T18:17:16+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-12T18:17:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10622"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78785"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"create